---
title: Mole-Spiced Beef Tacos with Poblano, Heirloom Tomatoes, and Chipotle Crema
description: If you ask for a traditional mole recipe, you’ll get something with a very, very long list of fancy ingredients. Luckily, we’ve gathered everything for you and put it all into a spice blend that makes achieving mole’s deep flavors a cinch. It’s based around cocoa powder, cumin, chili powder, and smoked paprika, creating an earthy profile that’s perfect for the ground beef in these tacos that also come with chipotle crema, poblano pepper, and corn tortillas.
